## Rotation Policies

### Rotation Schedule

| Secret Type | Rotation Frequency | Automation |
|-------------|-------------------|------------|
| Database credentials | 90 days or on demand | Vault dynamic or script |
| API keys | 90 days | Manual or automated |
| TLS certificates | Before expiry | cert-manager, Let's Encrypt |
| Encryption keys | 365 days or on compromise | KMS rotation |
| Service account keys | 90 days | Automated where possible |

### Rotation Procedure

1. Generate new secret
2. Update in secrets store
3. Deploy application to pick up new secret (or use dynamic fetch)
4. Verify application works with new secret
5. Revoke old secret
6. Audit log confirms rotation

### Rotation Checklist

- [ ] Rotation schedule is documented
- [ ] Rotation is automated where possible
- [ ] Applications tolerate rotation (no long-lived caches)
- [ ] Old secrets are revoked after rotation
- [ ] Rotation is tested in staging

