## Least Privilege

### Secret Access Control

| Role | Access |
|------|--------|
| Application (prod) | Only prod secrets for its service |
| CI/CD | Only secrets needed for build/deploy |
| Developer | Dev secrets only, or none |
| Admin | Full access with audit |

### IAM Policy Example

```json
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": ["secretsmanager:GetSecretValue"],
  "Resource": "arn:aws:secretsmanager:*:*:secret:myapp/prod/*"
}
```

### Per-Service Secrets

- [ ] Each service has its own secret path or namespace
- [ ] No service has access to another service's secrets
- [ ] Shared secrets (e.g., DB) use separate read-only roles per consumer

